(* README *)

1 - Description
    -----------

    T004 provides a mechanized proof that the center column of the
    canonical single-seed Rule 30 trajectory admits no closed uniform
    eventual periodic tail.  The development relies on the standard
    libraries Arith, Bool, List, and ZArith.  The proof factors into
    three constructive phases and three corollary layers.

    The constructive core consists of Phase 1 (the seeded orbit, the
    No Progenitor Theorem, and the replay/compactness scaffold),
    Phase 2 (bounded seed-window realizations and the Original Sin
    Theorem), and Phase 3 (carrier transport and the direct uniform-tail
    impossibility theorem).  Phase 3 is the recommended semantic
    endpoint: it proves that no triple (R, T, P) with P > 0 can carry
    a uniform eventual periodic tail.

    The corollary sequence then packages that obstruction externally.
    Corollary 1 isolates the Faithfulness Hypothesis and derives
    eventual aperiodicity of centered windows.  Corollary 2 interprets
    the center strip as a binary real and derives irrationality.
    Corollary 3 classifies the finite reverse-predecessor-carrier
    ambiguity and proves that no observation-only tamper checker exists.


2 - Repository Tree
    ---------------

    .
    ├── README
    │
    │      (This file.)
    │
    ├── R01__Phase_One.v
    │
    │      Phase 1 theory unit: base dynamics, the seed, the
    │      No Progenitor Theorem, replay/admissibility data, and the
    │      compactness-conditional no-pure-periodicity route.
    │
    ├── R02__Phase_Two.v
    │
    │      Phase 2 theory unit: bounded seed-window realizations, the
    │      Original Sin Theorem, and the auxiliary compact-trap /
    │      hidden-support vocabulary.
    │
    ├── R03__Phase_Three.v
    │
    │      Phase 3 theory unit: mixed-periodicity impossibility,
    │      carrier transport, and realizability-facing corollaries.
    │
    ├── R04__1st_Corollary.v
    │
    │      First corollary layer under the Faithfulness Hypothesis.
    │
    ├── R05__2nd_Corollary.v
    │
    │      Second corollary layer.  It interprets the center strip as
    │      a binary real, proves presentation independence with the
    │      finite growing-pyramid recipe, and derives irrationality
    │      under the Faithfulness Hypothesis.
    │
    ├── R06__3rd_Corollary.v
    │
    │      Third corollary layer.  It classifies the finite
    │      reverse-predecessor-carrier ambiguity of the visible
    │      canonical observation and proves that no observation-only
    │      tamper checker exists.
    │
    ├── T004__Comprehension.v
    │
    │      Audit-facing proof index for the public T004 surface:
    │      the three constructive phases, the three corollary layers,
    │      and the principal semantic endpoints.
    │
    ├── T004__Extraction.v
    │
    │      OCaml extraction surface for finite windows, seeded
    │      prefixes, truncations, and assumption reporting for the
    │      principal theorems.
    │
    └── appendix
           ├── ObservedPeriodRefuter.ml
           │
           │      Extracted OCaml implementation of the finite
           │      observational period refuter for centered canonical
           │      windows.
           │
           ├── ObservedPeriodRefuter.mli
           │
           │      Generated OCaml interface for the extracted
           │      period-refuter surface.
           │
           ├── UniformTailWitnessChecker.ml
           │
           │      Extracted OCaml implementation of the bounded
           │      uniform-tail witness checker for candidate periodic
           │      tails.
           │
           └── UniformTailWitnessChecker.mli

                  Generated OCaml interface for the extracted
                  witness-checker surface.
